The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, May 15: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh is expected to convene a meeting of chief ministers of all states this month-end to give a final shape to the proposed Rs 15,000-crore revitalisation package of co-operative banks, Nabard managing director Y. S. P. Thorat said. Thorat, who played an important role in suggesting a set of stringent guidelines for co-operatives to become eligible for the bailout package, said states have to agree to the package and make their share of contribution.

 Mumbai, May 15: Nortel vice-chairman and chief executive officer William Bill Owens is in India to share his vision on the growth strategy prospectus chalked for the company. The visit will enable Nortel to compete with emerging companies in the Asean region, sources said.

 New Delhi, May 15: The Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) has outlined six measures that could take the country to a double-digit inclusive growth.

 New Delhi, May 15: The empowered committee today said tax is being evaded by a majority of traders even after the introduction of VAT by not issuing invoices. However, traders termed the charge as baseless.

 Mumbai, May 15: Shipping Corporation of India (SCI) is exploring options of listing its shares on foreign bourses in the medium-term.




